==Bosnian==
===Etymology===
From Old Church Slavonic '''zima''' ("winter") < Proto-Indo-European '''*gheim-''' ("snow", "winter"). Cognate with Sanskrit '''heman''' ("in winter"}, Hittite '''gimmanza''', Greek {{IPAchar|[[χεῖμα]]}}, and Lithuanian [[ziema]] (all meaning "winter"). Possibly related to Persian {{FAchar|[[زمستان|زِمِستان]]}} (zemestān).
===Noun===
'''zima''' {{f}}
#[[winter]]
#[[cold]] [[weather]] (regardless of the season)
#[[cold]]; [[coldness]]
